                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240407-39-victim407 t18240407-39-viclabel222"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18240407-39-crimeloc223">Sun-street, Bishopsgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18240407-39-crimeloc223" type="placeName" value="Sun-street, Bishopsgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18240407-39-crimeloc223" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240407-39-off220 t18240407-39-crimeloc223"></join>. On the 15th of March this flannel stood on a stool at the door. I saw a hand lift it off, there was a cry of Stop thief, and it was thrown down about three yards from my door, I picked it up.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240407-39-person409">
                  ROBERT 
                  WAY
               <interp inst="t18240407-39-person409" type="surname" value="WAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240407-39-person409" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240407-39-person409" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in Sun-street, I saw the prisoner in company with another man. I saw a lady looking into<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182404070020"></xptr>Mather's shop, and as soon as she entered the door the prisoner snatched the flannel. I was loaded or I could have stopped him. I called Stop him, he dropped it, and a person followed him towards Bishopsgate-street. I put my load into a shop, followed, and met him in the custody of Riley, and am certain that he is the person.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240407-39-person410">
                  WILLIAM 
                  RILEY
               <interp inst="t18240407-39-person410" type="surname" value="RILEY"></interp>
